<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7787> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7787" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. procos., 113-114. See MRR 1.538, 539, note 4. Sumner places him in Hisp. Ult. as praetor in 113 and as procos. until his death in battle in 111 (Orators 72).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3421> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3421" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Killed in battle (Cic. Verr. 2.4.56; App. Ib. 99)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3420> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3420" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "As Piso's successor in Spain, Galba, Consul in 108, held the praetorship at the latest in 111, Piso's command should be dated in 113 or 112 after Marius and before Galba in 111. See also on Silanus, 113, Praetors." .
